diff --git a/CHANGELOG.md b/CHANGELOG.md
index 56eb7b33..e4a040f0 100644
--- a/CHANGELOG.md
+++ b/CHANGELOG.md
@@ -2,6 +2,23 @@
 
 All notable changes are documented here, newest first. Hive ships frequent micro-releases (see [docs/RELEASING.md](docs/RELEASING.md#versioning-policy)): each `vX.Y.Z` git tag gets a `## X.Y.Z` section with terse bullets — no `[Unreleased]` accumulator. Versioning is [SemVer](https://semver.org): PATCH for fixes and small changes (the common case), MINOR for notable features, MAJOR for milestones.
 
+## 0.3.3
+
+Two coupled defects blocked `hive run` in Claude tmux mode against Claude Code 2.1.179 on a clean install of the `hive-cli` release gem. Both are fixed here; a 0.3.3 patch release is the intended vehicle (not published by this change).
+
+### Packaging
+
+- Fixed: `hive.gemspec`'s `spec.files` glob was `lib/**/*.rb` (Ruby files only), so the built gem shipped without `lib/hive/scripts/interactive_claude_wrapper.sh` and `lib/hive/scripts/stop_hook.sh`. `bash <missing-file>` exited instantly and killed the tmux session before Hive could inspect it (`claude_launch_failed` / can't find pane); the missing stop hook also meant `.done` / `result.json` were never written, so `exit_code_only` / `state_file_marker` waits hung to timeout. Added `lib/hive/scripts/**/*.sh` to `spec.files`.
+- Added a built-gem packaging guard (builds the actual `.gem`, inspects its contents) plus a lighter `spec.files` unit check so a runtime shell script referenced by `ClaudeLauncher` / `StopHookInstaller` can never again ship missing from the artifact.
+
+### Claude tmux ready detector
+
+- Fixed: Claude Code 2.1.179's idle prompt was not recognized. The caret line uses a non-breaking space (U+00A0) after `❯`, and the input box now ends with separator / caret / separator / footer. The detector matched `\s` after `❯` (which does not match NBSP) and only inspected the last 2 nonblank lines, so it missed the caret and timed out with "claude interactive prompt did not become ready". The ready line now uses `[[:space:]]` plus an explicit `\p{Zs}` alternation (Unicode separator space, incl. NBSP) and scans a wider tail window, requiring every line beneath the matched caret to be chrome (footer / decorative separator) so a stale `❯` in scrollback cannot read as ready.
+
+### Also
+
+- End-to-end validation note (not fixed here): daemon/systemd binary drift (`/usr/bin/hive` 0.3.1 vs `~/.local/bin/hive` 0.3.2) is tracked as separate local-setup / daemon auto-retry work.
+
 ## 0.3.2
 
 Setup, the Telegram bot, and TUI performance are the focus of this release. Selected agent backends now persist globally so new projects inherit them; the bot gains idea-by-default capture, a `/waiting` view backed by a daily pending-answer digest, task-id slash commands, and structured JSON errors; and TUI status polling now scales with the number of active tasks instead of the whole archive.
